Modshell - Command-driven scriptable Modbus utility
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. About software
-----------------

This is a utility that can be used on several operating systems,
which can communicate with connected equipment using Modbus/ASCII,
-/RTU and -/TCP protocols. The program can - even automatically -
read, write or copy data from one device to another (e.g. transferring
settings).

2. How to get installer package for my OS?
------------------------------------------
a. Visit homepage (see later) to download installer packages:

  operation system  arch.   package name
  --------------------------------------------------------
  DOS               i386    mdshell01.exe            (SFX)
                    i386    mdshell01.zip
  Linux             i386    modshell-0.1-i386.bin    (SFX)
                    x86_64  modshell-0.1-amd64.bin   (SFX)
                    armhf   modshell-0.1-armhf.bin   (SFX)
                    i386    modshell-0.1-i386.zip
                    amd64   modshell-0.1-amd64.zip
                    armhf   modshell-0.1-armhf.zip
  Debian GNU/Linux  i386    modshell_0.5-1_i386.deb
                    x86_64  modshell_0.5-1_amd64.deb
  Raspberry Pi OS   armhf   modshell_0.5-1_armhf.deb
  FreeBSD           i386    modshell-0.1.txz
                    amd64   modshell-0.1.txz       
                    (port)  modshell-0.1-FreeBSD-Port.shar
  Windows           i586    modshell-0.1-win32.zip
                    x86_64  modshell-0.1-win64.zip
                    i586    modshell-0.1-win32.exe
                    x86_64  modshell-0.1-win64.exe
                    i586    modshell-0.1-win32.msi
                    x86_64  modshell-0.1-win64.msi
  Source code       (src)   modshell-0.1.tar.gz

b. Download from Github

  $ git clone https://github.com/pozsarzs/modshell.git

c. Download from Debian repository

  set reporitory:
  $ sudo echo "deb http://www.pozsarzs.hu/deb/ ./" >> /etc/apt/sources.list
  $ sudo wget -q -O - http://www.pozsarzs.hu/deb/KEY.gpg | apt-key add -
  $ sudo apt-get update

  install:
  $ sudo apt-get install modshell

